apricot /ˈeɪprɪˌkɒt/

(apricots) 

1. N-VAR An apricot is a small, soft, round fruit with yellowish-orange flesh and a large seed inside. 杏 

例： ...12 oz apricots, halved and pitted. …12盎司的杏，切成了两半并去了核。 

2. COLOR Apricot is used to describe things that are yellowish-orange in colour. 杏色的 

例： The bridesmaids wore apricot and white organza. 女傧相们穿着杏色和白色的透明硬纱。

